subSubSection.paragraph:
Catenarius magdae

is distinct from 

C. daviei

in its more elongate cephalothorax (just longer than wide in 

C. daviei

), its more elongate third antennular peduncle article (shorter than the second article in 

C. daviei

), more slender antennal articles, subtle differences in the pereopod setation (notably the distal carpal setation of pereopod 
1
), and in having six (rather than five) segments in the adult uropod endopod.
